To de-radicalize decolonization in our organization, we are taking time to reflect on our position about the history of Canadian Craft and the role of cultural appropriation within Canada’s aesthetics. To review what materials exist, what needs improvement and expansion.

The conversation at large is about Canada’s historical and continued injustices and systematic discrimination against Indigenous people and communities - this conversation includes the arts and culture sector.
